Here's the complete implementation:

**Configure the request size limit** in `Program.cs`:

```csharp
// Allow up to ~11 MB at the server level so the 10 MB app-level
// check can return a friendly error instead of a 400 from Kestrel.
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o => o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 11 * 1024 * 1024);
```

**Add the endpoint** (also in `Program.cs`, after `var app = builder.Build();`):

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    const long maxSize = 10L * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB

    if (file.Length == 0)
        return Results.BadRequest("Empty file.");

    if (file.Length > maxSize)
        return Results.BadRequest("File exceeds 10 MB limit.");

    var ext = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();
    if (ext is not ".jpg" and not ".jpeg" and not ".png")
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are allowed.");

    // Also verify the content-type header
    var allowed = new[] { "image/jpeg", "image/png" };
    if (!allowed.Contains(file.ContentType, StringComparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
        return Results.BadRequest("Invalid content type.");

    var uploadsDir = Path.Combine(Directory.GetCurrentDirectory(), "uploads");
    Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsDir);

    // Use a random name to avoid collisions and path-traversal via crafted filenames
    var savedName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var path = Path.Combine(uploadsDir, savedName);

    await using var stream = File.Create(path);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName = savedName });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()          // required for non-browser API clients
.RequestSizeLimit(11_534_336); // per-endpoint override (~11 MB)
```

**Key points:**

- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** — since `UseAntiforgery()` is in your pipeline, `IFormFile` endpoints will reject requests missing the antiforgery token. This disables it for API clients. Remove this if your callers send the token.
- **`.RequestSizeLimit()`** — overrides the default ~30 MB limit per-endpoint. Set slightly above 10 MB so your own validation can return a clear error.
- **`Guid` filename** — prevents path-traversal attacks and name collisions; the original filename is never used on disk.
- Both the extension *and* `Content-Type` are validated for defense in depth.
